came into this experience with no expectations, intentionally keeping my heart and mind open to whatever was meant for me. After weeks of research and feeling quite overwhelmed by the number of YTT options out there, I’m so glad all roads pointed me to House of Om at Amertham. What drew me in was the fact that it was tucked away in the jungle, far from the distractions of central Ubud. I wanted full immersion, and this setting truly allowed me to be fully present.\n\nThe past three weeks have been life changing. The group I was part of was absolutely amazing it genuinely felt like we were meant to walk this journey together. There was such a deep level of support for one another, especially during the tougher emotional, mental, and physical moments.
